data.description: Steal of a Deal! This quality built, 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom custom home presents a thoughtfully designed split-bedroom floor plan with lots of living space indoors and out. The home features an abundance of natural light and desirable wood laminate and tile flooring. The home boasts a sizable formal living room as well as a large family room with a cozy brick corner fireplace. The generously proportioned country kitchen offers ample cabinetry for storage, a substantial pantry, breakfast bar, glass cooktop, self-cleaning double wall oven and a convenient pass-through window to the rear patio, perfect for backyard entertaining. Additionally, the home includes a formal dining room highlighted by a welcoming wood plank accent wall, paneled wainscoting and a view of the rear deck and yard, enhancing the charm of this space. Notably, the custom built-in bench-style seating offers concealed storage underneath for added convenience. The expansive owner's suite offers both space and tranquility, featuring a large walk-in closet and an  adjoining glass-enclosed, tiled patio that leads to the rear deck. Indulge in the en-suite bathroom, with dual vanities, a relaxing soaking tub and walk-in shower. These living spaces effortlessly transition through sliding doors onto one of two enclosed patios, out to the beautiful open deck and the private backyard with no homes to the rear (greenspace). An indoor laundry/storage room offers an additional touch of practicality and organization. The oversized 2-car garage offers ample room for storage, hobbies or workshop area. A chain-linked fenced area is the ideal space for four-legged friends to run and play. Conveniently located within minutes to shopping, dining, medical, World Equestrian Center, the Crystal Clear Rainbow River and more.  Easy access to Interstate 75 for commuting to Orlando and Gainesville, a easy drive to Dunnellon, Crystal River, The Villages and more. Ocala is the crown jewel of Florida, a thriving area to work and play, with new job opportunities or a great place to retire. With a total of 3,550 sq ft, this home presents an outstanding value and opportunity.  Updated roof, HVAC, Water Heater, and more.  Call today to schedule a viewing before it’s gone.
